What you need to know:

Insurance Regulatory Authority (IRA) said underwriters had concentrated their business in Nairobi with 83.2 percent of their premiums sourced from the capital.Mombasa makes up 4.7 percent of the premiums while Kiambu-1.7 percent, Nakuru-1.57 percent, Uasin Gishu 1.42 percent, Kisumu-1.22 percent and Nyeri-1.08 percent leaving the rest of the country unserved.